						<summary>

						<p>Broken Slab lying near the <hi rend="italic">hōmakuṇḍa</hi> in the Pañchaliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Bukka I, [1363-64 A.D.]</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 12[85], Pārthiva,</hi> other details being lost. The date is irregular. The given cyclic year corresponds to <hi rend="bold">1363-64 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers gifts of money and probably of land also, for worship and offerings in the temple of Mārkaṇḍēśvara by Sāḷa and others. The details of the gift cannot be made out. It refers to a <hi rend="italic">daṇṇāyaka</hi> as governing some division.</p>						

						</summary>
